Flag Calculator
---------------

Undo functionality
- As a user I want to be able to undo the select/deselect of the flags.

Redo functionality
- As a user I want to be able to redo steps previously undone by the undo functionality.

Button to Select All
- As a user I want to be able to select all flags at once.

Button to Select None
- As a user I want to be able to unselect all flags at once.

Load enums from UI
- As a user I want to be able to have a File->Open menu item that lets me select an assembly file, open the assembly browse window and then let me choos an enum to be loaded.

* Display only selected
- As a user I want to have a checkbox that displays only the selected items.

* Different background color for checked checkboxes
- As a user I want to see the chacked checkboxes with different background color.

* List the flag values from a enum
- As a use I want to see a list with the values of the flag enum.

* Type a number - display it
- As a user I want to be able to type a number from the keyboard and see it displayed in a text box.

* Type a number - update flags
- As a user I want to be able to type a number from the keyboard and see the corresponding flag values checked.

* Paste a number - display it
- As a user I want to be able to paste a number from the keyboard (Ctrl+V) and see it displayed in a text box.

* Paste a number - update flags
- As a user I want to be able to paste a number from the keyboard (Ctrl+V) and see the corresponding flag values checked.

* Check/uncheck flags
- As a user I want to be able to check/uncheck the flag values displayed and to see the number updated.

* Copy the number
- As a user I want to be able the copy (Ctrl+C) the number displayed in the text box.

* Dinamically load enum
- As a user I want to be able to specify an enum type in the config file that will be dinamically loaded when app starts and be used as a source for the list of flags.
1239